TASK: Fix Space (pause/resume) in Contour Studio grow mode. Currently pressing Space does nothing visible — the grow animation keeps running.

The current code in contour_map_view.cpp uses SIGSTOP/SIGCONT via ContourBridge::pause()/resume(). The problem is likely:

1. The subprocess is launched via `sh -c "python3 ..."` so SIGSTOP goes to the shell, not the python process
2. Or the pipe reader keeps polling and the timer keeps firing even when paused
3. Or the key handler condition isn't matching

The fix should:
- Actually stop the animation when Space is pressed in grow mode
- Resume from the exact frame when Space is pressed again
- Show PAUSED in the status bar and button strip when paused
- The simplest approach may be: stop reading the pipe (skip pollPipe) when paused, rather than trying to SIGSTOP the subprocess. Or use process group kill.

Files:
- app/contour_map_view.cpp (key handler around "Space — pause/resume", pollPipe, bridge pause/resume/start)
- app/contour_map_view.h (bridge class, isPaused flag)

Build: cd /Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos && cmake --build ./build --target wwdos -j$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu)

Constraints:
- Keep the SIGSTOP/SIGCONT approach but send to process GROUP (negative pid) so the python child gets it too
- OR alternatively, just skip pollPipe() when bridge_.isPaused() — simplest fix
- Both approaches are fine, pick whichever is more robust
- Do NOT remove the pause/resume methods, just make them actually work
