**Preparing concise final summary**
[stderr] codex
Implemented a minimal fix that keeps `pause()/resume()` and makes them effective for grow mode by signaling the subprocess **process group** instead of only the shell PID.

**What changed**
- In [`app/contour_map_view.cpp`](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/contour_map_view.cpp:77), child now calls `setpgid(0, 0)` before `execl(...)`.
- In [`app/contour_map_view.cpp`](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/contour_map_view.cpp:86), parent also calls `setpgid(pid_, pid_)` to reduce race risk.
- In [`app/contour_map_view.cpp`](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/contour_map_view.cpp:96), `pause()` now does `kill(-pid_, SIGSTOP)`.
- In [`app/contour_map_view.cpp`](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/contour_map_view.cpp:103), `resume()` now does `kill(-pid_, SIGCONT)`.
- In [`app/contour_map_view.cpp`](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/contour_map_view.cpp:110), `stop()` now sends `SIGTERM/SIGKILL` to `-pid_` as well.
- Updated comments in [`app/contour_map_view.h`](/Users/james/Repos/wibandwob-dos/app/contour_map_view.h:37) to reflect process-group signaling.

**Why this fixes Space pause/resume**
- The command is launched via `sh -c ...`; previously signals hit only the shell.
- Sending signals to `-pid_` reaches both shell and Python child, so grow animation actually halts/resumes from current frame.
- Existing UI logic already shows paused state via `bridge_.isPaused()`, so `PAUSED` indicator and pause button highlighting continue to work as intended once pause is effective.

**Verification**
- Build command succeeded:
  - `cmake --build ./build --target wwdos -j$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu)`
- `ctest --output-on-failure` did not run tests because test binaries are missing in this build dir (`command_registry_test`, `scramble_engine_test`, etc.).
